"acode triggers"
"@WSYNTAX:@n

aset trigger <value>       : sets the type of trigger

@WVALUES:@n

@Wtime@n : execute trigger at specified MUD clock time.
@IIf value is >= 0, execute when (minute+60*hour) == value.
@IIf value < 0, execute every abs(value) minutes of MUD time.
@I@I(every minute of MUD time is about 6 seconds real time)
@IValid variables: room.

@Wsun, moon@n : execute trigger according to astronomy.
@IIf value < 0, execute when sun/moon sets.
@IIf value > 0, execute when sun/moon rises.
@IIf value == 0, execute when sun/moon reaches its zenith.
@IValid variables: room.

@Wleaving@n: execute when someone tries to leave the room.
@IFlags: directions to match.
@IValid variables: ch, room, exit.
@IContinue: allow ch to leave.
@IEnd: abort ch's movement.

@Wcast@n: execute upon casting a spell in the room.
@INote: executed before any matching object or mob cast triggers.
@ITarget: spell name to match (optional).
@IValid variables: ch (caster), victim (target), obj (target), exit (target),
@Iarg (spell name), room (caster).
@IContinue: allow the spell to take effect.
@IEnd: prevent the spell from taking effect.

@Wdescribe@n: execute when room or rextra description needed.
@ITarget: rextra keywords, blank for room description.
@IValid variables: room, ch, arg.
@IContinue: show default description.
@IEnd: show no description.

@Winit@n: execute at MUD startup time before reset. See 'acode trigger init'
@IValid variables: room.

@Wreset@n: execute after a room is reset.
@IValid variables: room.
@IContinue: set reset0, reset1, and reset2 rflags.
@IEnd: do not set reset0, reset1, and reset2 rflags.

@Wpath@n: execute before a mob tries to move along a path.
@IValid variables: ch, room, exit, victim (summoner).
@IContinue: go ahead and try to move.
@IEnd: stop the path, return to wandering.

@WSEE ALSO:@n
acode(, aset, aflag, aedit,acode triggers, variables, opedit, opset
"
