"check_skill"
"@eSYNTAX@n

check_skill( char, skill, chance )

@ePARAMETERS@n

char - pointer to character
skill - name of a skill
chance - integer, modifies difficulty level

@eRETURNS@n

Zero if skill fails
Nonzero if skill succeeds

@eDESCRIPTION@n

check_skill performs a random check, based on the character's skill level,
whether use of a specific skill will succeed.  If the \"chance\" parameter is
zero or absent, the basic probability of success is ( 10*skill_level - 5 ). 
Thus, the chance of success is 0% at level 0, 5% at level 1...  and 95% at
level 10.

If the \"chance\" parameter is positive, it indicates the percentage chance of
immediate success.  So for example, if chance == 50, the chance of success is
50% at level 0, 52.5% at level 1, ...  and 97.5% at level 10.

If the \"chance\" parameter is negative, it indicates the chance of immediate
failure.  So for example, if chance == -50, the chance of success is 0% at
level 0, 2.5% at level 1, ...  and 47.5% at level 10.

@eEXAMPLE@n

if( check_skill( ch, climb, 10 ) ) {
  send_to_char( #char, ch );
  act_notchar( #room, ch );
  transfer( ch, find_room( 24048 ) );
  use_skill( ch, climb );
  act_notchar( #arr, ch );
}

See also: use_skill.
"
