"Clans"
"@C@bSYNTAX@n

@Gclans@n               : lists all publicly known clans
@Gclans -f <acronym>@n  : Starts a new clan
@Gclans <name>@n        : lists charter/members of a listed clan
@Gclans -o <option>@n   : toggles clan options assuming permission
@Gclans -n <name>@n     : sets the full name of clan
@Gclans -l <level>@n    : sets the minimum level required to join
@Gclans -c@n            : edits the clan charter
@Gclans -a <acronym>@n  : changes the clan acronym
@Gclans expel <name>@n  : expels a member from the clan

@C@bDESCRIPTION@n

Clans are organizations developed to accomplish some purpose.  Because of
their added organizational structure they are accorded certain additional
privileges such as the right to build a @bstronghold@n.  Clans can serve great
purposes or small ones depending on what their intent is however whatever
purpose they serve the banding together of a clan requires that certain
restrictions be met.

@GRequirements To Create A Clan@n
@I@b*@n The Clan Leader (starting up the Clan) must be at least level 20.
@I@b*@n You must recruit at least 5 people to join and have them swear @Ballegiance@n.
    (all 5 must be level 10 or greater)
    (clans of fewer than 6 total members will be warned)
    (warned clans that don't reach 6 members soon will be removed)
@I@b*@n The Clan must have an established charter (see below).
@I@b*@n There is a starting fee of 20 platinum.

   A clan also has an Acronym when created to identify it.  This acronym
   should be a short form of the Clan's full name for easy identification.


@GA Clan's Charter Will Include:@n
@I@b*@n The Clan's Full Name - Clan's Acronym should be derived from this.
@I@b*@n The Clan's history/background - what brought about a need for it.
@I@b*@n What are its goals? - What is its purpose, what will it do?
@I@b*@n How will the clan achieve those goals in-game?
@I@b*@n Clan hierarchy - Officer positions and requirements
@I@b*@n Clan Rules - What are the laws/rules internal to the Clan
                 What are the rights/benefits of being a member?
@I@b*@n Joining Requirements - Including race/class/level restrictions.

Get to know the editor, the Clan charter will need to be easily readable and
presentable before it will be approved.


@GRestrictions@n
@I@b*@n Clans may have good members or evil members, but not both.
     Good/Neutral or Evil/Neutral are allowed.
     (In the case of a clan that takes its members from a single race
      or single class alignment @bmay@n be overlooked)
@I@b*@n Certain races may not be in a clan together.
     - elves/vyans typically may not be in the same clan.
     - dwarves/goblins typically may not be in the same clan.
     (In the case of a clan that takes its members from a single
      alignment or single class racial barriers @bmay@n be overlooked)
@I@b*@n The minimum level for clan members is level 10.
@I@b*@n The minimum level for clan leaders is level 20.


@GOther Options Available@n

Using the clans -o function the following flags can be set for the clan:

 Exist.Known - All players will be able to read your clan charter.
               Turning this off makes your clan anonymous.
 Members.Known - All clan members will have the clan name displayed on @bwho@n.
               Turning this off makes your clan membership anonymous.


@GThe Clan Building Checklist@n
@I@b*@n Prospective clan leader uses @bclan -f <acronym>@n to create the clan.
@I@b*@n Prospective clan leader uses @bclan -c <text>@n to create the charter
@I@b*@n Prospective clan leader uses @bclan -o <flag>@n to toggle settings.
@I@b*@n Make sure everything from \"A CLan's Charter Will Include\" is included.
@I@b*@n Make sure the charter is neat (@bclans -c spell@n helps spelling)
@I@b*@n 5 or more players use the @ballegiance@n command to join.
@I@b*@n Prospective clan leader contacts the imm in charge of Clan's for approval.

@GPost-Approval Checklist@n
@I@b*@n Clan leader needs to use the @bcedit@n command to set clan positions.
    (If they take too long the clan will be unapproved)

Additional questions and concerns regarding clans should be addressed to
@GTalis@n via @brequest@n or mudmail.

See also: @eallegiance@n, @ecedit@n, and @estrongholds@n.
"
"@C@bIMMORTAL NOTES@n

@Gclans delete <clan_name>@n  : Delete a clan
@Gclans -o@n : To set flags for clan restrictions and approval.

Cedit is used for setting flags on clan leaders / permissions.
"
