"Dam_message"
"@CSYNTAX@n

dam_message( char, dam, string, char2 )
fire_message( char, dam, string, char2 )
shock_message( char, dam, string, char2 )
cold_message( char, dam, string, char2 )
acid_message( char, dam, string, char2 )
magic_message( char, dam, string, char2 )
mind_message( char, dam, string, char2 )
sound_message( char, dam, string, char2 )

@b@WPARAMETERS:@n

char   - Pointer to character being damaged
dam    - Integer value of damage to be translated into damage string
string - String to display as cause of damage
char2  - Optional pointer to character dealing the damage

@b@W@CDESCRIPTION@n:@n

Displays a message to the room describing damage done to char.  This
function does no actual damage, it only gives notice that damage was done
(See \"help inflict\").

If string is plural, start it with a + so that the messages are displayed
correctly.  See the examples section below for clarification.

If the string starts with * (after any leading +), the attacker's (char2's)
name is omitted from the messages.  Optionally, char2 may be omitted
altogether for a similar effect (but see below).

Whether each character in the room receives the message is controlled by their
\"Damage.Mobs\" and \"Damage.Players\" flags--see \"help message\".  If char2 is
specified, char2 (usually the attacker) will always receive the message.

NOTE: the dam_message() call must be *before* a corresponding inflict() call,
for the displayed messages to be correct.

@b@WRETURNS:@n

none

@b@WEXAMPLES:@n

dam_message( ch, i, \"the crushing rock\" );

Would display to ch:
\"the crushing rock mauls you\"
Would display to everyone else in room:
\"the crushing rock mauls whomever\"

dam_message( ch, i, \"+the grue's biting teeth\" );

Might display:
\"The grue's biting teeth maim you.\"

dam_message( victim, i, \"crazy swing\", ch );

Might display:
\"Your crazy swing maims someone.\"
\"Attacker's crazy swing maims someone.\"
\"Attacker's crazy swing maims you.\"

to include a plural while using the char2 parameter the string should be
preceeded with +*.  Example:

dam_message( victim, i, \"+*the thrashing claws\", ch );

Might display:
\"Your thrashing claws maim a sheep.\"
"
