"Hierarchy of the Gods"
"In the beginning, there were the three.  Algesa and Ulthi, the balancing
forces of law and chaos, and Meriada, the eternal.  The three crafted the
universe and into it brought the four elemental forces to craft the world,
Essyn the Air, Kantos the Earth, Kryoth the Fire, and Osse the Water.  The
world was chaotic, a sphere of pure elemental power running loose without law
or reason.

Ulthi flourished in this chaos, but Algesa and Meriada sought to bring order
to this new world.  They created the Ancients to tame the world and as they
did so, Ulthi grew anger at the power that was stolen from him.  He became
jealous and twisted and evil, the first evil ever to enter the universe.  Ever
Ulthi's balancing counterpart, Algesa became the first force of good in the
universe.

There were five original ancients, Taranth, Kerog, Lonil, Temohpab, and
Neughlen.  Taranth brought peace into the world, calming the elements.  Lonil
brought light into the world, creating the sun.  Temohpab tamed the darkness,
calming all of the dark places Lonil could not reach.  Kerog protected the
order from falling back into chaos.  Neughlen was responsible for creating
life to populate the world.

Things did not continue so perfectly for long.  The unity of the Ancients was
broken first when Ulthi corrupted Temohpab.

Together, Taranth and Kerog had three daughters, Tarafas, the Dawn Star,
Tarayla, the Evening Star, and Anor, the Child-Goddess.  Together, Tarafas and
Tarayla created the elves.  As told in @YThe Twins@n, their unity was broken
by Temohpab, causing Tarafas to leave the world and Tarayla became Shantara,
allying with Temohpab and baring him three children, Morr, Morkith, and
Xiroce.  As told in @YThe Child-Goddess@n, Anor's innocence was lost at the
same time.  Anor fell in love with Lonil and bore two children, Ashallan and
Slen.

Meanwhile, Neughlen mated with three of the four elementals.  She bore Duroth
to Kantos, Sst'rasa to Osse, and Freylia to Essyn.  Duroth, with affinity with
the earth, created the dwarves and gnomes.  Sst'rasa, with affinity with the
scaled creatures of the land and sea, created the lizardfolk, though he
designed them to live on land to escape Osse's control.  Freylia, saddened by
the loss of her child friend Anor, created the childlike Thenne, later known
as halflings.

The three brothers, Morr, Morkith, and Xiroce were among the youngest of the
Ancients, with the same level of power as the tricksters, Ashallan and Slen,
until they caught the attention of the original three.  Meriada chose Morr to
control the threshold between life and death.  Xiroce was chosen by Algesa to
watch over the afterlife and every creature to pass through Morr's hands. 
Ulthi chose Morkith and imbued him with the power to hold the dead in the
world and bring forth demons from other dimensions.

Cynnis, daughter of Tarafas, returned to the world to watch over her mother's
forests.  Ashallan and Slen were divided by an arguement that has never been
settled, Ashallan joining Temohpab while Slen remained with her father.  With
the quiet influence of Ulthi, Neughlen gained a fascination with mixing the
attributes of different creatures to make new ones and creating smaller and
smaller life forms of great power, creating the first diseases and all kinds
of terrible monsters.  This brought strife between Neughlen and her three
children, especially Duroth and Freylia, as Neughlen swore allegiance to
Temohpab.
