"Junk_obj"
"Topic:   junk_obj

@CSYNTAX@n

@b@Gjunk_obj@n( object, number )

@Gobject@n - Pointer to object to remove
@Ginteger@n - Optional number of objects you want deleted

@CDESCRIPTION@n

Removes an object from the game.

The \"number\" argument is optional, but care must be taken when omitting it. 
If it's zero or omitted, the number of objects deleted depends on how many
were \"selected\" by the event which called the acode, mprog, or oprog.
For many triggers, this number will be 1.

This may sound straightworward, but it's not.  For example, consider the \"get\"
trigger, assuming there are 5 apples in the room, and the player types \"get
3*apple\".

If the apple has a \"get\" trigger, the number \"selected\" could be 1, 2, or 3,
because there are many reasons the first 3 apples might not be combined into a
single data object in memory, even if they are all the same object type. 
However, if some of the apples *are* combined, the trigger will only be called
once for the combined object.  Moreover, the \"selected\" count may be fewer
than the total number of combined objects.

So, normal usage is junk_obj( obj, 1 ).

See also: has_obj
"
