"New Continent Project"
"A new continent will begin construction once the Chiiron Farm, Hydras, and
Dark Chiiron are completed.  It will be a very large scale project, hopefully
with contributions by everyone, and I (Elfir) would like to think it'll be the
killing blow to all those other clones out there.  Enough gloating, here's the
plan so far:

1.  A boat will go from the Medienne docks to a small harbor at the
north-eastern edge of the new continent.  To ride the boat players will have
to either buy a ticket or stowaway, and stowaways will need hide or
invisibility to manage that.  The boat leaves at a certain time each day, not
when the players get on, unlike the fisherman at grems, and will travel for a
little while before reaching the other side.  This wait will not be painful
because there's an entire ship to explore and loot and an entire crew to talk
to.  I want people to realize that this place is far away.  Also encourages
them not to jump back and forth all the time.

2.  The harbor on the continent will be a very small town, with a trading
post, a bar, an inn, and fishermen.  At this point, only half, at most, of the
mobs are human.  Humans have not really settled here and just have this little
trade town as an attempt to profit off the place, but with little success.

3.  A vast plainsland spreads out south from the harbor, territory of a tribe
of nomadic halflings.  There are a few solitary wemics but it shouldn't be too
dangerous for a cautious level 10 to cross alone.  Areas are within and all
around this plainsland, most anything you can think of so long as it fits in
the plainsland ecosystem somewhat.  Enough of it should be mundane for it not
to look like a zoo.

4.  At the western border of the plains is a goblin farming village at the
base of a large mountain range.  The goblins are at perpetual war with the
halflings and on a cliff far above live perytons which pick off the strays on
both sides.

5.  Somewhere to the south of the plains is a very Neughlenish bog, full of
hybred monsters, strange disease, and all sorts of fun things.  Lots of room
for creative monsters in here.

6.  Along the eastern edge of the plains is a very large forest.  Somewhere
deep within is an old temple to Ulthi which caused many things to twist around
weirdly and chaos unbalances law.  There is an old castle in there, Euldemere,
whose denizens are all chaotic and have been for generations, a place so
chaotic it's lawful.

Each region needs to be built as well as areas within the regions, especially
the plains.  It should be less annoying to write the plains if we are instead
connecting many smaller sub-areas.  If you have an idea for something you want
to add, mail it to me and I'll help figure out how exactly it should fit into
the continent.  The final product should fit together like a puzzle, no oddly
placed areas and no weird themes out of the blue.
"
