"object limits"
"@eDESCRIPTION@n

Objects have a field 'limit' that controls how many of that item
are allowed to exist - the mud enforces this including instances in player
files.  The default limit is -1, meaning 'no limit.' A limit of zero means
that none can exist - it essentially disables pops of the item.  An object
with a limit of 1 is unique.  Only one can exist at a time.  When it is junked
(and the junk list has time to clear) or otherwise destroyed, another can
exist.
ofind has a new flag -# for searching for limited objects.  Example: 'ofind -#
0-' will find all limited objects.

Resets of the item will always fail if the limit would be exceeded.  oload( )
will fail if the limit would be exceeded.  replace_obj( ) will fail if the
limit would be exceeded.

The oload command can be used to exceed the limit. It will print a warning.

See also: obj_count, obj_limit
"
