"oiflag"
"@eSYNTAX@n

oiflag <object>
oiflag <object> <flag toggled>
oiflag -S <object> <flag>
oiflag -R <object> <flag>

@eDESCRIPTION@n

Where oflag will toggle a flag on all version of an object, oiflag will toggle
the flags on a specific instance of that object.  The object in question must
be in your inventory.  This is most commonly used to resize custom race items
after a player remorts.

Notice that the <flag toggled> field is optional.  Without it, the command
will show the current flag settings on the object in question.

The -S and -R options will set or remove the flag on ALL instances across the
MUD, including those in player files on disk.  This induces significant lag,
and should only be done when absolutely needed.

@b@WEXAMPLE@n

If we have a customed belt formerly owned by a halfling who remorted as a
human:
oiflag belt          \\Verify the belt is flagged halfling
oiflag belt halfling \\Remove the halfling flag from custom size
oiflag belt human    \\Set human flag for custom size

See also: oistat, oiset
"
""
