"oiset"
"@eSYNTAX@n

oiset [-a] <object> <field> <new_setting>

@eDESCRIPTION@n

Where oset is used to change the settings on every version of the item in the
game, oiset only changes the settings on a perticular instance of an item.
The item in question must be in your inventory.

By default, oiset changes one instance of the object, no matter how many may
be consolidated together.  The -a option causes all instances in a
consolidated group to be modified.  The number in the group can be seen using
oistat.

@b@WEXAMPLE@n


oiset longsword singular ouchystabbythingy

This will change the singular of the longsword in your inventory to
ouchystabbythingy without changing the singular of any other longswords of the
same item type.

See also: oistat, oiflag
"
