"Playtesting is one of the stages of area creation.

The gist is, at some basic simulation of the monsters and treasure reset
rates which are in an area from a player's view.

Some schools of thought:
- Pit similar level mobs against your new mobs.
- Create dummy players for playtesting (Player1, Player2, etc)
- Use real players

When using real players, it is important to use people who will both try
to break the area and can be trusted.

General rules for playtesting with real players:
- All eq and gold received is to be junked.
- Deaths which are not from bugs will not be reimbursed
- Keep the XP which you get (see above for opposite)
