"quest_standards"
"@bQUEST STANDARDS@n

After spending a great deal of time looking over the existing quests it was apparent there was no real order to the manner in which they were made.
This is intended to be a means by which quests can be more uniformly made.

@bQuest Points@n
Quest points should reflect the difficulty of the quest.

If a quest has no real level of challenge (perhaps just run from point A to
point B and fetch an unguarded item) it should only have 1 quest point.  There
should still be some effort involved.  Perhaps the item is in another city or
something or doesn't have a 100% respawn rate in one place.

Just because a quest is higher level doesn't mean it has to have a bigger
quest point value.  A quest that requires a player be level 50 but is only
fetch an item from Medienne and hand it to someone in Chiiron is still only
worth 1 quest point unless its dangerous to get the item.
Most often, however, higher level quests involve larger guardians and are
tougher to accomplish in which case they should be worth more points.  Look at
existing quests to determine how many points a quest should be worth.

If a quest has a tangible reward at the end it should be worth slightly less
than it normally might.  Perhaps one or two points depending on how nice the
item/reward is.  That doesn't mean a reward should mean no quest points, they
have done the work and deserve the points as well just perhaps not as many.

"
