object.  To place this restriction, set the race_specific oflag, and then set
the oflag(s) for the races that can wear the item.  Players whose races are
not set, and all mobs of non-player races or whose race oflag is not set, will
be unable to wear the item.

Please @edo not@n leave gaps in your race size oflags.  For example, don't
make an item that can be worn by gnomes and trolls, but not races sized in
between.  If you want something that a race can't use for reasons other than
size (like a dwarf-skull girdle, for example) use anti- flags, not size flags.

Note that race_specific does not prevent resetting an item on a mob that is
the wrong race.  However, if the mob ever removed the item, it would never be
able to wear it again.

