"search acodes"
"With exception to dummy acodes (acodes which you search but never pop
anything), most search acodes follow a simple formula:

if( !is_player( ch ) )
@n  end;
if( rflag( reset0, room ) ) {
@n  remove_rflag( reset0, room );
@n  if( random( 1, 10 ) == 1 ) {
@n    act_tochar( #find, ch );
@n    act_notchar( #rfind, ch );
@n    obj_to_char( oload( 162 ), ch );
@n    }
@n  else {
@n    act_tochar( #nothing, ch );
@n    };
@n  }
else
@n  act_tochar( #nothing, ch );

The top part is self-explanitory..  pets/familiars should not be used as
a pop-by-proxy device.  First, there is a check to see if the room
repopped.  If that passes, it removes the room flag.  Next, a 'chance' is
rolled to see if the character gets the item he/she was looking for.  If
he/she rolls a 1, the item pops, thus making the item pop at about a 10%
rate.  (find and rfind are the strings sent to the player/others)

There are variations on this theme, of course.  If, for example, you
wanted multiple items to pop off of the same search acode, you could
modify the 'chance' roll to look something like this: 

