"Trap Construction"
"Traps are special objects, rather than acodes.  To construct a trap,
oedit new as any other object.

Set the object type to trap, then set the various fields such as cost and
repair as you see fit.  Remember to write a description, as many traps
can be acquired and used by players.

Next, create an object program using 'opedit new'.  Use 'opset trigger
use' to set the opcode to the use trigger, which is necessary for the
trap to function correctly.

From there, it is a simple matter of constructing the opcode to display
the appropriate messages and cause the desired damage or effect.

One important consideration is whether the trap will hit only once or
will hit again and again until disarmed.  Although this is left to the
builder's discretion, the vast majority of traps will hit only once and
then will be inactive.  Traps that hit repeatedly should be both very
rare and used only in special occasions.  To have a trap hit only once,
the last line of the opcode should be - 

junk_obj( obj, 1 );

This removes the trap object from the room and thus, in effect,
deactivates the trap.

To have the trap strike repeatedly, simply omit this line.  For examples
of traps and their code, see 'ofind -t trap'.  Some examples of basic
traps are the poison needle (vnum 130), and the magic missile trap (vnum
3406).

See Also: oedit, Trap Placement
"
