"Trap Placement"
"Traps are special objects that reset inside container objects and that
can be disarmed by a thief who is sufficiently learned in the Untrap
skill.

To place a trap in an object:

- Reset the object, for example a chest, in the room.
- Type 'reset # +c' to flag the object as a container.  The # is
whichever reset slot the container uses.  For example, if a chest is the
first reset in a room, the command would be 'reset 1 +c', if it is the
third reset 'reset 3 +c', and so on.
- Oload and reset the trap you wish to use.  Various traps can be found
using the 'ofind -t trap' command.
- Flag the trap as being inside the container using the 'reset # +i' command.
- Set the chance for the trap to reset.  (See 'help reset' for
information on this).  For example, if a trap is reset at 10%, then the
chest in which it resets has a 10%, or 1-in-10 chance of being trapped.

See Also: reset, trap construction
"
