"Wear Locations"
"This help file provides a listing of wear locations.
CREATED ON 8 JUNE 2001

take, finger, neck, body, head, legs, feet, hands, arms, waist, wrist,
right.hand, left.hand 

The 'take' location means the item can be placed into the inventory.
The 'right.hand' is similar to 'main weapon'.
The 'left.hand' is similar to 'off hand', also shield, torch, etc..

LAYERS

All objects have bottom, under, base, over, and top layer flags.

One of these flags must be set for the item to be worn.

If multiple flags are set, more than ONE of these items can be worn, ONE
in each location.  (note this is different than I remember, which used to
be TWO in each location.  This way makes MUCH more sense.) 

ADDITITVE

The 'additive' oflag determined if wearing multiple identical items keep
adding their magic affects.

MORE ON LAYERS

For rings and bracelets, remember, that this applies individually to EACH
finger or wrist.  (you can wear an item in each wear location on both
left and right side).

For right.hand and left.hand the ONLY layer flag which should be used is
BASE, as it does not make any sense whatsoever to be holding more than
one item in each hand.

WHERE SHOULD MY ITEM GO?

FINGER: rings and wedding bands, etc.  Magic items should have ONLY the
'base' layer flag.  This means that characters may only wear at MOST TWO
magical rings at the same time.  Non-magic trinkets should user the
'bottom' layer flag ONLY.  This allows characters to where TWO trinket
rings and enables them to remove all magic rings independantly of trinket
rings.  No other use of any other layer for the finger location is
approved for mortal use.

NECK: necklaces, medallions, charms, pendants, collars, scarves, etc. 
Magic necklaces, medallions, and charms should have ONLY the 'base' layer. 
Trinkets use the 'bottom' layer ONLY.  Collars and scarfs, etc, use the
'top' layer.  No other use of neck layers is allowed.

BODY: cloaks, armor, shirts, armor pads, etc.  All base armor should have
the 'base' layer ONLY.  This applies to plate mail, leather armor, chain
mail, robes, shirts of type armor, etc, etc.  All cloaks and 'trinket'
(read: non-magic and very cloaklike) robes use the 'over' layer ONLY. 
This does not apply to robes of type armor!  The 'top' layer is reserved
for backpacks.  The 'under' layer is to be used for armor pads, 'trinket'
(read: non-magic, for dress only) shirts and dresses, etc.  The use of
the 'bottom' layer is prohibited at this time.

HEAD: helms, chain coifs, turbans, masks, etc.  All helms, hats, and
armor crowns should have the 'base' layer ONLY.  Coifs and circlets
should have the 'under' layer only.  Arming caps should have the 'bottom'
layer ONLY.  Trinket crowns (read: non-magical, status only) should have
the 'over' layer ONLY.  Headdresses, etc, have the 'top' layer.  For now
(this is hoping to change), earrings, feathers, etc, must share the 'top'
layer with headdresses.

LEGS: pants, skirts, leggings, kilts, underwear, etc.  Underwear is
reserved for the 'bottom' layer (pun intended).  Leg armor pads are for
the 'under' layer, also 'trinket' pants.  The 'base' layer is for armor,
such as pants of type armor, leggings, leg plates, etc.  The 'over' layer
is for 'trinket' skirts and kilts.  There is no intended use for the
'top' layer.

FEET: anklets, socks, shoes, spurs, sandals, boots, etc.  The 'bottom'
layer is for anklets.  The 'under' layer s for socks.  The 'base' layer
is for ALL shoes, boots, sandals, etc, etc.  The 'over' layer is for
spurs.  There is no use for the 'top' layer (no pennyloafers).

HANDS: gloves, manacles, gauntlets, etc.  All gloves and gauntlets go in
the 'base' layer.  Manacles, chains, etc go to the 'over' layer.  No
other layers are assigned.

ARMS: sleeves, arm tattoos, arm guards, over-the-shoulder bags (quivers,
etc) etc.  The 'bottom' is for 'trinket' bands, brands (permanent),
tattoos (permanent), etc.  The 'under' layer is for armor pads.  The
'base' layer is for all sleeves, arm guards, arm plates, arm armor, etc. 
The 'over' layer is for over-the-shoulder items like quivers and satchels.

WAIST: belts, girdles and etc.  All items go on 'base' layer.  An
exception is that keyrings may be clipped to an invisible belt on the
'top' layer.

WRIST: bracelets, bracers, wrist bands, etc.  The 'base' layer is for all
bracers.  The 'over' layer is for all bracelets (magic or trinket).

EAR: earrings ('base'), feathers ('top').
HAIR: ribbons, barettes, pins.  (all 'base').
(note that currently both ear and hair share the 'top' layer on head.)
"
