"worn"
"@eSYNTAX@n
worn( ch, wear_part [, wear_layer] );

@ePARAMETERS@n
ch - character/mob
wear_part - the wear slot of the object being sought
wear_layer - the layer of the object being sought

@eDESCRIPTION@n
Returns the object worn on a particular wear part for a particular layer.  If
no argument is supplied for wear_layer, the object in the bottommost layer
will be returned.

See const wear_part for valid wear locations and const wear_layer for valid
layers.

@eRETURNS@n
The object found at that layer, or null if no object was found.

@eEXAMPLES@n
// Moves backpack/blanket into inventory
obj_to_char( worn( ch, body, top ) );

// Junks whatever a player is holding as a weapon (base layer)
junk_obj( worn( ch, right_hand, base ) );

@eERRORS@n
None.
"
