"Write"
"@C@bSYNTAX@n

write              : writes the current area file
write [-f] all     : writes all files
write [-f] areas   : writes all area files
write <field> ...  : writes the files specified by fields

Allowed Fields = { areas, mobs, objects, help, trainers, shops, tables,
notes, quest, rtable, world, dictionary }

@C@bDESCRIPTION@n

Saves the various files to disk.  Be careful with \"write all\" as it produces a
decent amount of lag.  If no field is specified the default is the area you
are in.

The \"-f\" flag forces all areas to be written, regardless of whether they've
been modified.

See also: lag, save
"
